			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">End-of-life treatment</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Waste water treatment</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Groundwater remediation refers to the process of treating natural water found below the Earth's surface to remove contaminants. This water is typically located in aquifers, which are underground layers of water-bearing permeable rock, rock fractures, or unconsolidated materials. Remediation technologies include a variety of in situ and ex situ methods that are selected based on the specific conditions and types of contamination. Nanoscale materials have been developed for environmental site remediation, targeting issues like chlorinated solvents or oil spills. The goal of groundwater remediation is to restore the water to a condition suitable for use, often as part of a response to a confirmed contamination incident.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">地下水修复是指对地表以下的天然水进行处理以去除污染物的过程。这些水通常位于地下蓄水层，即地下含水透水岩层、岩石裂缝或未固结材料。修复技术包括各种原位和非原位方法，根据具体条件和污染类型进行选择。针对氯化溶剂或石油泄漏等问题，已开发出纳米级材料用于环境场地修复。地下水修复的目标是将水恢复到适合使用的状态，这通常是已确认污染事件应对措施的一部分。</common:generalComment>
